meaningMnemonic: Things that are <kanji>target</kanji>ed as <vocabulary>Japanese</vocabulary> are more than just Japanese, they are <vocabulary>very Japanese</vocabulary>. This word may be hard to understand at first, but there are many things the Japanese consider to be Japanese-only. These theories range from reasonable to ridiculous, but either way, you'll see them described as 日本的.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well. It will help if you know how to read 日本 as well.
